cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about language modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces a novel theoretical framework for better learning, which involves reducing the number of trainable variables. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses the Penn Treebank dataset, which is commonly used in NLP research involving recurrent neural networks, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves sequence prediction.
